Package commands

package commands
This package contains the classes that represent the commands that the user can use to interact with the application.
  • Class
    Description
    Clear
    Command for clearing the collection.
    Command
    Abstract class for a command.
    Command.IllegalArgumentsNumber
    Exception for illegal number of arguments.
    CommandRunner
    The CommandRunner class is responsible for running the commands.
    CommandRunner.ExitCode
    The exit code of the command.
    ConsoleCmdCommand
    Abstract class for a command that uses console input/output and the command manager.
    ConsoleCollectionCommand
    Abstract class for a command that uses console input/output and operates on a collection.
    ConsoleCommand
    Abstract class for a command that uses console input/output.
    ExecuteScript
    Command for executing a script from a file.
    Exit
    Command for stopping the program without saving to file.
    FilterByEndDate
    Command for filtering the collection by end date.
    Help
    Command for displaying help for available commands.
    History
    Command for displaying the history of commands (last 13 used).
    Info
    Command for showing information about the collection.
    Insert
    Command for adding a new element with a given key.
    RemoveAnyByEndDate
    Command for removing the element by end date.
    RemoveGreater
    Command for removing all elements greater than the given one.
    RemoveGreaterKey
    Command for removing all elements greater than the given key.
    RemoveKey
    Command for removing an element from the collection by its key.
    Save
    Command for saving the collection to a file.
    Show
    Command for printing all elements of the collection to the standard output stream.
    Update
    Command for updating the value of an element in the collection with a given id.
